docs.description:
Secondary completion rate. Urban is the total number of urban students of any age in last grade of secondary school, minus the number of urban repeaters in that grade, divided by the number of urban children of official graduation age. The completion rate can exceed 100 percent if there are many overage students in the last grade of secondary school. 
DHS: Secondary completion rate. Urban
